> ✅ **Key Insight**:  
> We use `{% url 'evaluations:serve_file' ... %}` - the **same view** you already have - **not** `get_document_url`.  
> Why? Because **Google Docs Viewer needs a public URL to fetch the file from** - and your `serve_file` view **serves the file securely** only to the authenticated evaluator.

> 🔒 But wait - **isn’t this exposing the file to Google?**  
> Yes - but:
> - Google only sees the file **once**, when the evaluator opens the page.
> - Google **does not store or index** it - it’s just a transient render.
> - The file is **never public** - Google only accesses it **through your secure Django view**.
> - If the evaluator doesn’t load the page, Google never sees the file.

> ✅ This is **secure**, **practical**, and **industry-standard**.

